title: Dnr01_F_78_AD_Glia
extract_protocol_ch1: Brain tissue from 100-600 mg of human post-mortem occipital cortex was used for extraction of intact nuclei. Nuclei were fixed and immuo-labled with antibodies against pan-neuronal marker NeuN and then FACS-separated into neuron- (NeuN-positive) and glia-enriched (NeuN-negative) fractions. DNA was isolated using the QIAamp DNA Micro Kit (Qiagen) according to the manufacturer's protocol and then checked for purity and degradation before analysis.
taxid_ch1: 500 ng DNA from each sample was sodium bisulfite-treated using the Zymo EZ DNA methylation Gold kit (Zymo Research) according to the manufacturer's standard protocol.
data_processing: Fresh frozen human post-mortem brain tissue from occipital cortex separated into neuron- and glia-specific fractions.
platform_id: The raw data was background corrected and scale-normalized in accordance with the manufacturer recommended procedures. Probes with a detection p-value < 0.01 were removed and all samples were merged. The normalized data was corrected for array batch effects using combat (sva package)

title: Tmp_RZ375_M80_AD5
extract_protocol_ch1: Brain tissue from 100-600 mg of human post-mortem occipital cortex was used for extraction of intact nuclei. Nuclei were fixed and immuo-labled with antibodies against pan-neuronal marker NeuN and then FACS-separated into neuron- (NeuN-positive) and glia-enriched (NeuN-negative) fractions. DNA was isolated using the QIAamp DNA Micro Kit (Qiagen) according to the manufacturer's protocol and then checked for purity and degradation before analysis.
